Interface ExpressionArgument

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AndOperator, BooleanExpressionArgument, Expression, NotOperator, OrOperator

    public interface ExpressionArgument
    Interface for operands and operators that appear in the expression stack.
    See Also:
    Expression

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      ExpressionArgument evaluate(Expression expression, Object input)
      This method is called when an argument in the expression stack is evaluated.

    • Method Detail

      • evaluate

        ExpressionArgument evaluate(Expression expression,
                          Object input)
        This method is called when an argument in the expression stack is evaluated. The method Expression#evaluate(Object input) is used to evaluate the entire stack.
        Parameters:
        expression - The expression stack the argument is in.
        input - The input argument to the expression stack.
        Returns:
        The resultant value to push back on the stack.
        See Also:
        Expression
